beforeRouteEnter.name: beforeRouteEnter
beforeRouteEnter.description:
Guard called when the router is navigating to the route that is rendering
this component from a different route. Differently from `beforeRouteUpdate`
and `beforeRouteLeave`, `beforeRouteEnter` does not have access to the
component instance through `this` because it triggers before the component
is even mounted.

tags.name: param
tags.text: to - RouteLocationRaw we are navigating to

tags.name: param
tags.text: from - RouteLocationRaw we are navigating from

tags.name: param
tags.text:
next - function to validate, cancel or modify (by redirecting) the
navigation

1.type: (this: undefined, to: RouteLocationNormalizedGeneric, from: RouteLocationNormalizedLoadedGeneric, next: NavigationGuardNext): _Awaitable<...>

beforeRouteUpdate.name: beforeRouteUpdate
beforeRouteUpdate.description:
Guard called whenever the route that renders this component has changed, but
it is reused for the new route. This allows you to guard for changes in
params, the query or the hash.

tags.name: param
tags.text: to - RouteLocationRaw we are navigating to

tags.name: param
tags.text: from - RouteLocationRaw we are navigating from

tags.name: param
tags.text:
next - function to validate, cancel or modify (by redirecting) the
navigation

beforeRouteLeave.name: beforeRouteLeave
beforeRouteLeave.description:
Guard called when the router is navigating away from the current route that
is rendering this component.

tags.name: param
tags.text: to - RouteLocationRaw we are navigating to

tags.name: param
tags.text: from - RouteLocationRaw we are navigating from

tags.name: param
tags.text:
next - function to validate, cancel or modify (by redirecting) the
navigation

21.name: initialState
21.description:
Use this option to optionally pass initial state to the table. This state will be used when resetting various table states either automatically by the table (eg. `options.autoResetPageIndex`) or via functions like `table.resetRowSelection()`. Most reset function allow you optionally pass a flag to reset to a blank/default state instead of the initial state.

Table state will not be reset when this object changes, which also means that the initial state object does not need to be stable.
